---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: 'Webflow',
    slug: '/comparisons/framer-vs-webflow'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Squarespace',
    slug: '/comparisons/framer-vs-squarespace'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    webflow: 'Best for pixel-perfect custom design',
    squarespace: 'Best for easy templates with support',
    winner: 'Webflow for design control, Squarespace for ease'
};

---

<Layout title="Webflow vs Squarespace: Visual Design vs Template Ease">

  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'Webflow vs Squarespace: Visual Design vs Template Ease',
      description: 'Webflow is a visual design platform for pixel-perfect control. Squarespace is the template leader for easy websites. Both target designers but with different philosophies. Here\'s the breakdown.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/webflow-vs-squarespace'
    }}
  />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">Webflow vs Squarespace:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Control vs Convenience</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Webflow gives designers pixel-perfect visual control—build anything without code. Squarespace offers polished templates with zero learning curve—pick a theme, customize, launch. Both target designers but with completely different approaches.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Webflow if you want complete design control and custom interactions.<br />
            Use Squarespace if you want polished templates with a simpler workflow.<br /><br />
            Webflow wins on flexibility. Squarespace wins on speed and support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Webflow is a visual design platform. Design in the browser with pixel-perfect control. Create custom layouts, animations, interactions—all visually. The code is generated automatically. It's powerful but has a steep learning curve.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Squarespace is a template-based platform. Pick from hundreds of professional templates, customize with a visual editor, launch. The templates constrain what you can do, but the learning curve is gentle. It's for designers who want speed over total control.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Webflow:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.webflow}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Squarespace:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.squarespace}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Webflow</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Squarespace</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Design control</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Pixel-perfect custom</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Template-based</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Webflow</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Learning curve</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Steep</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Gentle</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Squarespace</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Build speed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Slow (custom)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Fast (templates)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Squarespace</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Animations</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Unlimited custom</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Template-dependent</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Webflow</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">E-commerce</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Advanced</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Strong</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Tie</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$23-212</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$16-65</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Squarespace</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Webflow wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Complete design freedom</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Webflow lets you build anything. Custom layouts, unique interactions, complex animations—no constraints. Squarespace templates are beautiful but limit what you can customize. If your design vision is unique, Webflow is the only choice.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Advanced interactions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Scroll-triggered animations, complex hover states, micro-interactions—Webflow's interaction designer is unmatched. Squarespace has animations but they're built into templates. For premium interactive experiences, Webflow wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">CMS capabilities</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Webflow's CMS is powerful—custom content types, dynamic collections, filtering, referencing. Build complex content structures visually. Squarespace has blogging and simple collections but can't match Webflow's CMS depth.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Squarespace wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Speed to launch</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Pick a Squarespace template, replace images and text, launch in hours. Webflow requires building from scratch—design, structure, interactions. For tight deadlines, Squarespace is significantly faster.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Customer support</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          24/7 support with phone, chat, and email. Squarespace has supported millions of websites for 20 years. Webflow has support but it's not as comprehensive. If you need hand-holding, Squarespace wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Template quality</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Hundreds of professionally designed templates tested on real sites. They're polished, conversion-optimized, and beautiful out of the box. Webflow has templates too but they're less curated than Squarespace's.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>So which should you use?
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Webflow if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You want complete design control</li>
          <li>You need custom animations and interactions</li>
          <li>You're building complex content structures</li>
          <li>You're willing to invest time in learning</li>
          <li>Client work requires pixel-perfect output</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Squarespace if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You need to launch quickly</li>
          <li>You want professional templates out of the box</li>
          <li>You value 24/7 customer support</li>
          <li>You're newer to web design</li>
          <li>Your budget is under $50/month</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Webflow and Squarespace both target designers but with different philosophies. Webflow gives you total control—build anything, but invest time learning. Squarespace gives you speed—beautiful templates, but work within constraints.<br /><br />
          For custom portfolios, agency sites, complex brands—Webflow's flexibility shines. For local businesses, restaurants, quick client work—Squarespace's template approach wins.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href="/comparisons/framer-vs-webflow" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Compare Framer vs Webflow
          </a>
          <a href="/comparisons/framer-vs-squarespace" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Compare Framer vs Squarespace
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

</Layout>
